-- Milan's CityLife Real Estate Project Obtains $1.7 Billion-Euro Financing
-- Chiara Remondini
-- 2010-06-29T14:47:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-29/milan-s-citylife-real-estate-project-obtains-1-7-billion-euro-financing.html

          
          
             Milan’s CityLife real-estate project
that includes the tallest building in Italy signed a 1.4
billion-euro financing with banks led by Eurohypo AG,
Commerzbank AG’s property-lending unit.  
 Banca IMI, Banca Popolare di Milano Scrl, Credit Agricole
SA,  Mediobanca SpA and UniCredit SpA are the other financing
banks, according to an e-mailed statement today.  
 CityLife investors include Allianz SE of Germany and
Assicurazioni Generali SpA in Italy.  
          
          


  


        